commit.message:
Downgrade log level on "Unsupported condition"

The "Unsupported condition" are quite common on modern Intel CPUs. It's
also expected as thermald doesn't have proper support for those conditions (and probably never will).

So lower the log level to make it less scary.

Fix seg fault when there is no config file

thermald currently segfaults on its first run.

If a configuration file is missing, `cthd_acpi_rel::generate_conf`
will invoke `cthd_acpi_rel::parse_target_devices` without a prior call
to `cthd_acpi_rel::process_psvt`, which is the only place that
initializes the `psvt_data` and `psvt_count` variables and both are
read uninitialized, which results in a segfault. Unlike its art and
trt counterparts, the two variables are not initialized in the
constructor.

Release 2.5.5

Refer to README.txt for changes.

Process a single trip in a zone with a target state

When there is a single trip in a zone which calls for setting a
specific target state, that is not enough to cool the system. Any
temperature above should be treated as a trip without any target state.

This helps thermal shutdown in Alder Lake desktop system.

Fix incorrect ioctl numbers used for reading PSVT

The current thermald source code uses ioctl numbers that are
inconsistent with those used by the acpi_thermal_rel driver in the
linux source tree. The effect of this mismatch is to cause a stack
smash when running thermald against linux 6.5.3.

commit.message:
Change the sorting order when min_max_valid

The current sorting order is picking based on the max power settings,
which has opposite affect.
For example if there is a table like this with ITM:
target:\_SB_.PC00.LPCB.ECDV.SKIN  trip_temp:46 pl1_min:45000 pl1.max:76000
target:\_SB_.PC00.LPCB.ECDV.SEN5  trip_temp:60 pl1_min:15000 pl1.max:45000

If first SKIN temperature is >= 46, then range for PL changes is from
76W to 45W.
While the above condition is active if SEN5 >= 60, the range is from
45W to 15W. So the loweest PL1 should go upto 15W.

With current sorting the lowest PL1 will be 45W, as in the sorted list
SKIN will be above SEN5. Hence, SKIN will own RAPL for controls till
skin temp < 60.

So change the order so that in this case SEN5 will be before SKIN.
